  tool: read_file
  output: # guarantee-single-result-when-row-found

## Procedure
When extracting an answer from a uniquely specified row (such as the last or latest entry), always ensure that if the row exists in the table, the answer is emitted—not left blank. Only emit an empty answer if no matching row exists.

## Example (Python)
```python
matches = df.loc[df[query_col] == query_value]
